Aage Teigen (17 July 1944 – 15 January 2014) was a Norwegian jazz musician (trombone) and economist born and raised in Oslo. He was from a number of orchestras and active on the Oslo jazz scene.
He initiated the Oslo Jazzfestival and led the festival between 1986 and 2007.
Teigen received the Oslo City Culture Award in 2002 for his efforts for the Oslo Jazzfestival.
Han mottok Oslo Jazzfestivals pris Ella prize in 2011.
